      "body" : "I agree that returning the hash might not be sufficient for some use cases, but it's better than nothing.\r\n\r\nIdeally, being able to lock the mempool and/or the blocks would be great (even tho I can't really think of any use case where one wants to lock just the mempool and not the blocks) - but, as Alekos was saying, it seems to be a bit complicated to implement. ",
